        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 3:47PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 347 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Keysville, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph, heavy rain, and frequent
lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Reduced visibility and minor flooding
possible. Frequent cloud to ground lightning strikes.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southeastern Prince
Edward, northwestern Lunenburg and west central Nottoway Counties,
including the following locations... Briery Creek Lake, Prince Edward
Station, Briery, Arvins Store, Twin Lakes State Park, Nutbush,
Scholfield, Kingsville, Virso, and Meherrin.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
